 12
 13 Questions to answer at top of client.c:
 14 (You should not need to change the code in client.c)
 15 1. What is the address of the server it is trying to connect to (IP address and 
 16 port number). The server address is 127.0.0.1 and the port is 8000. 
 17
 18 2. Is it UDP or TCP? How do you know?
 19 It is TCP because the socket is created using SOCK_STREAM.
 20
 21 3. The client is going to send some data to the server. Where does it get this 
 22 data from? How can you tell in the code? 
 23 The data comes from the terminal (user input), because the program reads from STDIN_FILENO using read(). 
 24 
 25 4. How does the client program end? How can you tell that in the
   code? 
 26 The program ends when the read loop stops, which happens when read() returns 1 
 27 or less. After that it closes the socket with close(sfd) and exits.
 28
 29
